      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks. Could you expand on that a bit? Specifically, when you say the judge would weigh his \"socioeconomic disadvantages,\" do you think those factors actually make it more likely that someone like Profile B gets a harsher sentence in practice, compared to Profile A? Like, would the court see his background as a reason to be more punitive because of the \"risk\" he poses, or would they see it as a reason to be more lenient?",
